  "prompt": "What is implicit function?",
  "response": "An implicit function is a function where the relationship between variables is defined by an equation, but the function cannot be easily solved to express one variable explicitly in terms of the others.\n\nKey characteristics of implicit functions:\n\n1. Definition:\n- Defined by an equation F(x, y) = 0\n- Not directly solved for y or x explicitly\n- Relationship between variables is implicit\n\n2. Example:\nx\u00b2 + y\u00b2 = 1 (represents a circle)\nThis equation defines y implicitly as a function of x\n\n3. Types:\n- Single implicit function\n- Parametric implicit function\n- Multivariate implicit function\n\n4. Differentiation:\n- Requires implicit differentiation technique\n- Involves treating y as a function of x\n- Uses chain rule and derivative rules\n\n5. Characteristics:\n- Complex, non-linear relationships\n- Often used in advanced mathematics\n- Represent curves, surfaces in coordinate systems\n\n6. Applications:\n- Geometry\n- Physics\n- Engineering\n- Computer graphics\n- Advanced mathematical modeling\n\n7. Visualization:\n- Can represent more complex relationships\n- Not always easily graphed or solved algebraically\n\nUnderstanding implicit functions requires advanced mathematical skills and techniques.",
